methods.name: newService
methods.desc: newService creates a new service for a merchant

args.name: sender
args.desc: The address the plugin currently controls

args.name: asa
args.desc: The asa to be used for the subscription

args.name: amount
args.desc: The amount of the asa to be used for the subscription

args.name: passes
args.desc: The number of accounts the subscription can be shared with

args.name: cid
args.desc: The ipfs cid of the subscription contract

args.name: allowTraversal
args.desc:
Indicates whether the user can downgrade
or upgrade the subscription to a different service from the user without losing their streak

methods.name: pauseService
methods.desc:
pauseService pauses a service for a merchant
it does not shutdown pre-existing subscriptions
it simply prevents new subscriptions from being created
for a specific service

args.name: sender
args.desc: The address the plugin currently controls

args.name: index
args.desc: The index of the box to be used for the subscription

methods.name: activateService
methods.desc: activateService activates an service for a merchant

methods.name: shutdownService
methods.desc:
shutdownService permanently shuts down an service for a merchant
it also shutsdown pre-existing subscriptions

args.name: sender
args.desc: The address the plugin currently controls

args.name: index
args.desc: The index of the box to be used for the subscription

methods.name: isShutdown
methods.desc: serviceIsActive checks if an service is shutdown

methods.name: block
methods.desc: block blacklists an address for a merchant

args.name: sender
args.desc: The address the plugin currently controls

methods.name: unblock
methods.desc: unblock removes an address from a merchants blocks

methods.name: isBlocked
methods.desc: isBlocked checks if an address is blocked for a merchant

args.name: merchant
args.desc: The merchant address to be checked
